        "content": "Append-only log of direction flips and key level breaks. One bullet per material change.\n\n---\n\n- **2026-04-17 (run 20260417_233350):** Signal Buy (confidence 70%). ADX 41, RSI 91 (deeply overbought), hourly STC cross bearish. Setup: parabolic momentum, Z-score 3.66. Entry limit $278.26, target $305, stop $270. Order placed; never filled (limit missed the continuation run to $353 ATH). Prior setup: no prior recorded signal.\n\n- **2026-04-30 (run 20260430_140858):** Signal flipped Buy \u2192 Hold (confidence 52%). AMD ran from ~$245 (Apr 15) to ATH $353 (+76% in 21 days) \u2014 limit entry $278.26 from prior run was never revisited. R/R unfavorable at current price ($337\u2013$345): 0.5:1 at immediate resistance ($352.99), sub-2:1 even to Fib 1.272 ($366.67). Earnings binary May 5 adds tail risk. Head trader: wait for confirmed breakout above $352.99 (1.5x+ volume) or pullback to $308\u2013$315 (~17.5:1 R/R at $312 entry). ADX 73.57, RSI 82, Z-score 2.47 \u2014 trend intact but entry overextended.\n\n- **2026-05-01 (run 20260501_133540):** Key level broken \u2014 AMD closed at $354.49, above the 7x-tested $352.99 breakout trigger. However, breakout is volume-deficient: Apr 30 volume was 1.05x 20-day average vs. 1.5x minimum required (swing_breakout, run 20260501_133540). Breakout signal is invalid. Signal remains Hold (confidence 58%). RSI 83.06/86.46, Z-score 2.60 \u2014 overextension increased. Hourly ADX 15.89 (weak) diverges from daily ADX 74.94 (extreme strong) \u2014 intraday momentum fragmenting. Earnings binary May 5 veto confirmed. New two-way post-earnings framework: bull re-entry $316\u2013$335 (10 EMA zone), bear fade $355\u2013$368 on confirmed daily reversal candle with 2:1+ R/R.",
